<h1>@HI{{kai}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vplain{{}} (@HI{{no}}) @EM{{@HI{{kai}}}}.
<li> @Ai{{}} (@HI{{no}}) @EM{{@HI{{kai}}}}.
<li> @Anastem{{}} (@HI{{na no}}) @EM{{@HI{{kai}}}}.
<li> @N{{}} (@HI{{na no}})@EM{{@HI{{kai}}}}.
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{kai}}}} is a sentence ending particle which marks a "yes/no" question in informal male speech.
The preceding sentence must be in the plain form.
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{kai}}}} is only used for "yes/no" questions. For sentences involving an interrogative,
<a href="grammar-particle-dai.html">@HI{{dai}}</a> is used.
</p>

<p>
In the sentence patterns above, the @HI{{no}} appears where formal speech would have used <a href="grammar-n-desu.html">@HI{{ndesu}}</a>.
</p>

<p>
The equivalent sentences in female informal speech would be formed by dropping @EM{{@HI{{kai}}}} and using a rising intonation.
</p>

